reviews.review_text: awesome nice upgrade, really cool and rare fire on the mountain without scarlet prelude
9-24-87 Sweet show. High quality C Miller remaster.
SWEEEEEEEEEET Eighties are the BEST, and '87 is the BEST of 'em all.  BRING IT YOU EIGHTIES HATERS!
Bucket of All Buckets Uhh. . . if this isn't the best Hell in a Bucket ever, could somebody please point me to another one?  Bobby utterly goes OFF.

my highlights high time
My Brother Esau (great take)

P.land

There's no place like home Philly is home and the boys never let me down in the city of brotherly love..The HIGH TIME in the 1st set is ever so sweet! What an interesting 2nd set! so please>GIVE IT A WHIRL>Forever Grateful>Forever Dead!!!!!
Tease of Mexicali Why'd they stop...just weren't feeling it or what?  High Time hit me this time, Jer's advice is "Nothing's for certain; it can always go wrong."  That's MY Grateful Dead!
Best Bucket ever The high time isn't bad either, but let's keep the focus on what's important. I waited in line for almost ten minutes for these tickets, what a tribulation.

bucket envy i REALLY like this show for its verve and sound quality... love the esau>birdsong>promised to end set 1 and box 'o rain to open set 2... lovelight is excellent.... thx to all who made this avail in its GREAT sounding glory

Good Ol' Spectrum I know there's hundreds of nice longer,jammier intense O1's (circa 1967-74) but the Other One on this show is so psychedelic, spacey,and noodlely. Being there and in the moment, just one of my favorites... They just keep working around the theme in space heaven minurates....almost like Tangerine Dream came on stage and played out of space for 10 minutes....

Mexicali tease They play the entire Mexicali intro out of Me Uncle then Bob steps up and sings Big River!. Band concerts over and Jerry smokes the fills and leads. Box of Rain and Iko bring joy, Bob goes off on Bucket. Pleasing show from a time of optimism for the band
